column3: Does Go language use Copy-on-write for strings as in Java? I.e. if I pass a string by value to a method and never change it will this allocate memory and copy the string (which will be time inefficient) or it will just reference a single copy.
How can I use Go append with two []byte slices or arrays?
Is os.Getenv("HOME") the best way to obtain the running user's home directory in Go?
